<h1>Website structure</h1>

<p>Once you're comfortable creating articles it is time to consider how you will structure your website. Website structure refers simply to the framework in which your content is presented and how you might best group your articles.</p>

<p>Each web page or 'article' created needs to be linked to in order for users to find them. Users visiting the website need markers and directions to find content that they might find useful or interesting and it is helpful if articles are grouped in a way that makes sense and flows naturally.</p>

<p>There are many approaches to structuring a website but perhaps one of the most common is a home page leading to 'gateway' pages which in turn lead to content pages or articles.</p>

